./sdp/logs/Verify_T-001_20260416T054258Z_1776346678.log:2157:+sdp/logs/Lead_T-005_20260408T223256Z_1775690077.log:41:{"type":"message","timestamp":"2026-04-08T23:14:40.445Z","role":"user","content":"# Task T-005@20260408T223256Z: Add local infinite-quota short-circuit to `quota_monitor.py` so provider `\"local\"` always returns 1.0 headroom and is never rate-limited.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- `get_agent_headroom(\"ollama\")` returns 1.0<br/>- Ollama is never excluded from selection due to quota<br/>- Tests verify infinite headroom for local provider\n\n**Tier:** T1 — Light (Bug fix / config change / minor update)\n\n## Instructions\n\nRead the project's ADP documentation and understand existing patterns before making changes.\n\n**ADP Phases:** Implement → Verify → Commit\n\n1. Implement the fix or change described above.\n2. Ensure all existing tests pass.\n3. Add a regression test if the bug was not previously caught.\n4. Commit with a descriptive message: `fix(scope): short summary [T-005@20260408T223256Z]`\n\n## Rules\n\n- No spec required. Task description + commit message is sufficient.\n- Existing tests MUST pass after your change.\n- Follow existing code patterns and conventions.\n- Do not modify files outside the scope of this task.\n- Log any concerns to ESCALATIONS.md.\n\n## Validation\n\nRun before committing:\n```bash\npip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x && ruff check src/ tests/ && mypy src/\n```\n\nAll must pass.\n"}
