./sdp/logs/Verify_T-001_20260416T054258Z_1776346678.log:2700:+sdp/logs/Verify_T-019_20260416T043834Z_1776324455.log:13656:sdp/logs/Verify_T-008_20260408T223256Z_1775692000.log:2159:The implementation has unit coverage for `bootstrap_identity` and name generation, including corrupt-file and persistence cases. Integration coverage is missing: there is no call site that runs bootstrap during system startup.
./sdp/logs/Verify_T-001_20260416T054258Z_1776346678.log:2701:+sdp/logs/Verify_T-019_20260416T043834Z_1776324455.log:13657:sdp/logs/Verify_T-008_20260408T223256Z_1775692000.log:2171:- [ ] Runtime does not call `bootstrap_identity` on startup, so identity files are not guaranteed to be created automatically on first boot (for example, startup loop creates `FirstBootAnnouncer` and then only reads identity for announcement). Severity: blocking
